nter;\"|76\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|Single transferable vote (Group voting ticket)\n|- style=\"background:#cc8899;\"\n!<u>[[2016 Australian federal election|43rd]]</u>\n!<u>2016</u>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|26\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|21 + (3 [[Liberal National Party of Queensland|LNP]])\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|3 + (2 [[Liberal National Party of Queensland|LNP]])\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n|&nbsp;\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|9\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|1\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|11\n| style=\"text-align:centre;\"|[[Family First Party|Family First]],<br />[[Jacqui Lambie Network|Jacqui Lambie]],<br />[[Derryn Hinch's Justice Party|Justice Party]], <br />[[Liberal Democratic Party (Australia)|Liberal Democrats]], <br />[[Nick Xenophon Team]] (3), <br />[[Pauline Hanson's One Nation|One Nation]] (4)\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|76\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|'''Single transferable vote ([[Optional preferential voting]])'''\n|- style=\"background:#eee;\"\n![[2019 Australian federal election|44th]]\n!2019\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|26\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|26 + (4 [[Liberal National Party of Queensland|LNP]])\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2 + (2 [[Liberal National Party of Queensland|LNP]])\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n|&nbsp;\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|9\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|1\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|1\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|5\n| style=\"text-align:centre;\"|[[Centre Alliance]] (2), <br />[[Jacqui Lambie Network|Jacqui Lambie]], <br />[[Pauline Hanson's One Nation|One Nation]] (2), \n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|76\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|Single transferable vote (Optional preferential voting)\n|}\n\n{{clear}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[2019 Australian federal election]]\n* [[Members of the Australian Senate, 2016\u20132019]]\n* [[Double dissolution]]\n* [[Women in the Australian Senate]]\n* [